goals.question: What is the geographic distribution of incidents in the LA riots dataset?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=15, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median Age: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the age distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Age")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=gender_counts.index, y=gender_counts.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('Gender')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(race_counts, labels=race_counts.index, autopct='%.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the racial distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title="Race", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Create a bar chart of incident types
    ax = sns.countplot(x='type', data=data, palette='viridis')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of incident types in the LA riots dataset?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Incident Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='Incident Types', loc='upper right', labels=data['type'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='type', palette='deep')
    plt.title('What is the geographic distribution of incidents in the LA riots dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Incident Type', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
